entry.et: French or Late Latin; French médical, from Late Latin medicalis, from Latin medicus physician, from mederi to remedy, heal; akin to Avestan vī-mad- healer, Greek medesthai to be mindful of mete

def.dt: :of, relating to, or concerned with physicians or the practice of medicine
:a public officer who conducts autopsies on bodies to find the cause of death
:of, relating to, or being a form of insurance designed to pay all or part of the medical bills of major illnesses usually after deduction of a fixed initial sum
